Constellium N.V Key Developments

Constellium N.V. Reports Unaudited Consolidated Earnings Results for the Second Quarter and Six Months Ended June 30, 2017; Provides Earnings Guidance for the Year 2017
Jul 27 17
Constellium N.V. reported unaudited consolidated earnings results for the second quarter and six months ended June 30, 2017. For the quarter, the company reported revenue of EUR 1,382 million against EUR 1,233 million for the same period a year ago. Income from operations was EUR 73 million against EUR 80 million for the same period a year ago. Income before income taxes was EUR 27 million against EUR 35 million for the same period a year ago. Net income attributable to equity holders of the company was EUR 16 million or EUR 0.15 per basic and diluted share against EUR 9 million or EUR 0.08 per diluted share for the same period a year ago. Net cash flows from operating activities were EUR 45 million against EUR 135 million for the same period a year ago. Purchases of property, plant and equipment were EUR 60 million against EUR 78 million for the same period a year ago. Adjusted EBITDA was EUR 127 million against EUR 107 million for the same period a year ago. Free cash outflow was EUR 21 million against free cash flow of EUR 57 million for the same period a year ago. Revenue increased 12% compared to the second quarter of last year due primarily to higher aluminium prices.

For the six months, the company reported revenue of EUR 2,710 million against EUR 2,383 million for the same period a year ago. Income from operations was EUR 173 million against EUR 133 million for the same period a year ago. Income before income taxes was EUR 67 million against EUR 46 million for the same period a year ago. Net income attributable to equity holders of the company was EUR 29 million or EUR 0.27 per diluted share against EUR 1 million or EUR 0.00 per diluted share for the same period a year ago. Net cash flows from operating activities were EUR 81 million against EUR 48 million for the same period a year ago. Purchases of property, plant and equipment were EUR 120 million against EUR 156 million for the same period a year ago. Adjusted EBITDA was EUR 220 million against EUR 199 million for the same period a year ago. Free cash outflow was EUR 54 million against EUR 125 million for the same period a year ago. Net debt was EUR 2,044 million at June 30, 2017, as compared to EUR 2,035 million at December 31, 2016. 

The company is updating Adjusted EBITDA growth guidance for 2017 to the high end of high-single digit range. The company continues to expect Adjusted EBITDA growth in the high single digits annually for the next three years, leading to over €500 million of Adjusted EBITDA in 2020.


Constellium N.V. Supplies 10 Millionth Part to Ford Motor Company
Jul 13 17
Constellium N.V. announced that it has delivered its 10 millionth part to Ford Motor Company. A provider of aluminum structural components for the Ford F-150 and Super Duty trucks, Constellium will also supply the all-new Ford Expedition starting in Fall 2017. Constellium provides several aluminum parts for the Ford F-150 and Super Duty, including the windshield header, a complex component that reduces weight as well as the number of parts required in comparison with the steel version it replaced. In Fall 2017, Constellium will begin supplying the all-new aluminum-intensive Ford Expedition from its Van Buren plant as well. The facility was expanded in 2015 to double its production capacity to accommodate the Ford projects. The 2018 model year Expedition saves 300 pounds compared to the previous model.


Constellium N.V to Report Q2, 2017 Results on Jul 27, 2017
Jul 10 17
Constellium N.V announced that they will report Q2, 2017 results at 9:00 AM, W. Europe Standard Time on Jul 27, 2017


