Industrial platform






About aluminium






 

Finance
Constellium is a global sector leader strongly committed to designing and manufacturing innovative and high value-added aluminium products and solutions for a broad range of applications dedicated primarily to aerospace, automotive and packaging markets.Constellium operates 24 manufacturing sites in Europe, North & Central America and China. The company’s Technology Center located in Voreppe, France, is the origin of Constellium’s advanced aluminium solutions in the automotive, aerospace, and packaging sectors.The company is headquartered in Amsterdam (The Netherlands) with corporate offices in Paris (France), Zurich (Switzerland) and New York (United States). Key figures 2016 










 










Full-Time EmployeesConstellium employs approximately 11,000 Full-Time Employees (FTE) 










BusinessA global activity through three business units:

 Aerospace and Transportation
 Packaging and Automotive Rolled Products
 Automotive Structures and Industry

Products

 Rolled products: plates, sheets and coils
 Extrusions: customized profiles, large profiles, soft and hard alloy profiles, tubes and bars
 Automotive structures: Crash management systems, other safety systems, cockpit carriers, body-in-white structural components
 Over 150 active patent families

Positioning

 #1 worldwide for aerospace plates
 #1 worldwide in closure stock
 #1 in North America for wide coils
 #1 in Europe for large profiles
 #2 in Europe for hard alloy extrusions
 #2 worldwide in Crash Management Systems (CMS)
 #2 shared in Europe in Auto-Body Sheet
 #2 in Europe for can body stock
 #3 in North America for can body stock



 



